In [[mathematics]], '''overconvergent modular forms''' are special [[p-adic modular form]]s that are elements of certain  ''p''-adic Banach spaces (usually infinite dimensional) 
containing classical spaces of [[modular form]]s as subspaces.  They were introduced by [[Nick Katz|Nicholas M. Katz]] in 1972.

